column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear  No Precipitation  Light Wind Blowing Upstream
column13: -Clear. No ice or show remains near river. Some logs in channel and running in willows on LHB.
column14: -RiverPro boat measurement ~20m upstream of gauge. -Initially comm issues with RiverPro even right at boat edge. No direct connect cable available. -Was about to abandon measurement but attempt with "Quick Measurement" button was successful. As test compass cal were part of seperate file and combined in QRev two measurement files uploaded. -only 11 minutes but did not do another two transects due to time constraints from pilot duty day. Do not consider to diminish accuracy of mmt. -MGH taken from DWL as sensor was settling and unstable during measurement. Readings from a second rod placed in water showed minimal change to stage throughout whole visit. - @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller 2016) 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -Cut taken at usual spot just downstream of gauge. -Level tie shows potential movement of holding BM by 0.005m. To be reviewed after next level tie. Does not change measurement plotting very close to curve. -Erratic trace reading to reading from OTT. Not observed on water surface and likely due to sensor facing slightly upstream. Unavoidable while deploying at this stage and velocity. Will reposition at lower stage. ADCP by Moving Boat

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy  No Precipitation  Moderate Wind Blowing Downstream
column13: -Some ice chunks still on shore. Water in willows and on LHB.
column14: -Tetheed boat mmt from John boat and 6hp -bottom track issues in consistent part of transect even after moving further downstream for second pair of transects. -QRev seems to have sorted most of the gaps out in transects. StreamPro may be unsuitable for this river at this stage although intensity velocity and depth all seem well within the StreamPro's ability. -moving bed expected. Review mmt for treatment of MBT issues that could not be resolved within limited timeframe on site. -@ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller 2016) 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ -DWL taken where line enters water -OTT offset 3.407 ADCP by Moving Boat
HG: 3.610 SRC: -0.003 No Reset (NR)

column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Cloudy  Light Rain  Calm Wind
column13: Open water conditons.  Water is visibly low.  Small gravel bar in front of gauge is breaking the water surface.
column14: Used the ARC boat to conduct measurement.  Had some initial problems with the ARC boat.  First time using open water River Surveyor software.  Not a pleasant experience and could have or may have been detrimental to the quality of the measurement overall.  Attempted transects roughly 30m below heli pad.  Not a great spot at this water level.  Moved downstreamed above the next split in the river.  Much better section.  Difficult to obtain edge estimate on far bank as the battery in the range finder seemed to be going dead.  Getting  38cms  Corrected M.G.H. includes Sensor Reset Correction of -0.003 and Gage Correction of 0.000 applied to Weighted M.G.H of 3.609 Used total station off of ground rod. ADCP by Moving Boat
MK 19JAN2022: Revised levels to run from primary BM 144. Originally run from 145 in field HG: 3.947 SRC: 0.011

Tech thought river was flowing in opposite direction. -Some slush observed in deepest sections -MGH to be determined after SRC obtained in future visit.  MGH 3.979 *checked LTN

Backwater conditions; complete ice cover. Roughness of jumbled ice in the gauge reach is more apparent this visit. River froze up very rough. Measured downstream ~1.5 km same section as Jan 26/16. Ice quite dirty. Slush encountered on only 1 panel. Max % Q @ Stn 7/P6=8.1%. Average ice thickness=0.66 m. Hot water used on ADCP transducer face. Sources:Manual
